# Bundled Endfield game data placeholder.
#
# This directory is empty in the git repo by design. It gets populated at
# package-build time (see .github/workflows/cd.yml, step "fetch bundled data")
# by downloading the latest endfield-tables.zip from 3aKHP/EndFieldGameData
# and extracting it here. The resulting npm package / Docker image then
# ships with a read-only data snapshot that serves as a fallback when the
# auto-sync directory is empty or the network is unavailable.
#
# At runtime, server.ts wraps this in a FallbackStore:
#   FallbackStore(primary=auto-sync-dir, fallback=./data/endfield)
# so reads prefer fresh synced data but transparently fall through to the
# bundled snapshot when synced files are missing.
#
# Do not commit actual data files here — they bloat the repo and go stale.
# The CD pipeline is the single source of truth for bundled contents.
